HEADWORD: Pedometer
<hw>Pe*dom"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Pedi-</ets>, <ets>pedo-</ets> + <ets>-meter</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>p⟦eacute⟧dom⟦egrave⟧tre</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Mech.)</fld> <def>An
instrument for including the number of steps in walking, and so
ascertaining the distance passed over. It is usually in the form of a
watch; an oscillating weight by the motion of the body causes the index
to advance a certain distance at each step.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pedometrical</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Pedometric</ent>⟦br⟧
